In this article, President Trump addresses the issue of sanctuary jurisdictions and their impact on public safety. He criticizes cities like San Francisco and Oakland in California, as well as New York and Denver, for refusing to cooperate with Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) and releasing criminal aliens into their communities. Trump argues that these actions are a direct threat to the safety of American citizens and calls on Congress to block funds for jurisdictions that shield dangerous criminals. He emphasizes the need to end the bloodshed caused by sanctuary policies and protect American lives and cities.